3. To induce the Europeans increasingly into a self-Finlandized attitude, in
                        part out of fear of the Soviet Union, and in part out of wishful thinking
                        that a genuine detente truly exists;

4. To prevent a rapid resolution of the Middle Eastern problem and to
                        increase U.S. difficulties, in the hope of radicalizing the Arabs and of
                        gaining greater leverage;
